}], "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"faf91280-8542-4fe4-b426-f3403c02a2d3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Tested with version:  13.2, 13.3 (2023), 14.1 (2024), 14.3 (2025) for Linux \
Ubuntu 22.04; 13.3 for Windows 11\n",
 StyleBox[" Known problems: ",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978426932648081*^9, 3.978426965445005*^9}, {
  3.978428740019491*^9, 3.978428744007998*^9}, {3.978700360583974*^9, 
  3.978700394124711*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"74e4b704-5f32-4f2c-a70d-\
f24458674016"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Some versions of Mathematica (e.g., the 14.x releases) generate compiled \
functions that execute substantially more slowly than those produced by \
earlier versions. In particular, performance issues have been observed for \
compiled code containing iterative constructs, such as ",
 ButtonBox["Do",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Do"],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["For",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/For"],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["Sum",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Sum"],
 ", and related loop-based operations within ",
 ButtonBox["Compile",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Compile"],
 ". In certain cases, functions compiled with Mathematica 14.x may run up to \
an order of magnitude slower than the corresponding functions compiled with \
Mathematica 13.x. To mitigate this issue, we provide the option to load \
precompiled functions generated using Mathematica 13.2."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9784280913566628`*^9, 3.97842831005862*^9}, {
   3.978428444810999*^9, 3.978428585839061*^9}, {3.978428667260242*^9, 
   3.9784286701223907`*^9}, {3.9784287083160152`*^9, 3.978428709394812*^9}, 
   3.978767106232527*^9, {3.9792941681634912`*^9, 3.979294168163622*^9}, {
   3.979881676903912*^9, 3.979881677476171*^9}, {3.979881729834981*^9, 
   3.97988187647301*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"703e28a3-a828-4dec-abc0-\
3e225036a911"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For ",
 ButtonBox["wbWeinUniCond",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    FrontEnd`FileName[{"Documentation"}, "wbWeinUNICond.nb", 
     CharacterEncoding -> "UTF-8"], None}],
 ",  ",
 ButtonBox["wbWeinUniNec1Cond",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    FrontEnd`FileName[{"Documentation"}, "wbWeinUNICond.nb", 
     CharacterEncoding -> "UTF-8"], None}],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["wbBrancUniCond",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    FrontEnd`FileName[{"Documentation"}, "wbBrancUNICond.nb", 
     CharacterEncoding -> "UTF-8"], None}],
 " and ",
 ButtonBox["wbBrancUniNec1Cond",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    FrontEnd`FileName[{"Documentation"}, "wbBrancUNICond.nb", 
     CharacterEncoding -> "UTF-8"], None}],
 ", we do not load precompiled functions, because they rely on external \
functions and may incur a larger performance slowdown than locally compiled \
versions. Although this issue can be mitigated by linking the appropriate \
libraries, the required library formats and linkage settings are \
operating-system dependent. To avoid potential incompatibilities, we \
therefore do not enable this linking by default."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9784280913566628`*^9, 3.97842831005862*^9}, {
   3.978428444810999*^9, 3.978428585839061*^9}, {3.978428667260242*^9, 
   3.9784286701223907`*^9}, {3.9784287083160152`*^9, 3.978428709394812*^9}, 
   3.978767106232527*^9, {3.979294179789041*^9, 3.979294215137661*^9}, {
   3.979294251409384*^9, 3.979294293657798*^9}, {3.9792943586227417`*^9, 
   3.979294382897156*^9}, {3.9792944166856127`*^9, 3.979294417437111*^9}, {
   3.979294475938574*^9, 3.97929448613162*^9}, {3.9793575518578033`*^9, 
   3.979357700254334*^9}, {3.9793577410453787`*^9, 3.979357743169239*^9}, {
   3.9793577872033052`*^9, 3.979357787203751*^9}, 3.979357847866255*^9, {
   3.9798808356374273`*^9, 3.9798808476992188`*^9}, {3.979880890390716*^9, 
   3.97988089039093*^9}, {3.97988092853179*^9, 
   3.9798810338139257`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e31f9650-ece3-4cc7-bce7-\
ff3075f39bc0"],

Cell["\<\
On multi-socket systems (e.g., workstations and servers), neural-network \
inference may be slow due to suboptimal thread and memory management settings.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.978428588719586*^9, {3.9792928822956142`*^9, 3.979292942135174*^9}, {
   3.9792929782774363`*^9, 3.979293016777055*^9}, {3.979293100054469*^9, 
   3.979293138176469*^9}, {3.97929322338097*^9, 
   3.9792932411642942`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"163c1da6-e2e1-41c5-9dc1-\
8a331fc8113a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

